#!/usr/bin/env bash
# ==============================================================================
# AcreetionOS Server — Welcome Message
# Displayed in a terminal window on first desktop login.
# Explains the mission, tools, release schedule, and how to help.
# ==============================================================================

MARKER="/etc/acreetionos-welcome-done"
USER_HOME="${HOME:-/home/$(whoami 2>/dev/null || echo admin)}"

# Only run once
if [[ -f "${MARKER}" ]]; then
    exit 0
fi

# Read the docs
MISSION_FILE="/usr/local/share/acreetionos/MISSION.txt"
TOOLS_FILE="/usr/local/share/acreetionos/TOOLS.txt"

cat > /tmp/acreetionos-welcome.txt << 'WELCOMEEOF'
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                                                                      ║
║            Welcome to AcreetionOS Server!                            ║
║            Arch-based. Just better. More stable.                     ║
║                                                                      ║
║            #KeepLinuxFree                                            ║
║            #AcreetionOSWillAlwaysBeFree                              ║
║                                                                      ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Thank you for choosing AcreetionOS.

Every major operating system vendor has decided that your computer is not
yours. They ship telemetry, ads, and AI features you didn't ask for. They
track what you do, sell your data, and lock you into walled gardens.

We don't.

AcreetionOS has:
  ✗ No telemetry
  ✗ No data collection
  ✗ No ads
  ✗ No "phone home" services
  ✗ No corporate agenda
  ✓ Just a libre, open-source OS that respects you

We offer the same powerful experience that big corporations have, to
people who truly deserve it — everyone.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

📅  RELEASE SCHEDULE

AcreetionOS Server follows an LTS-based Semi-LTS schedule with quarterly
ISO builds. Every January, April, July, and October a new ISO is built
automatically with the latest updates.

  Q1 (Jan) — LTS point release
  Q2 (Apr) — Maintenance release
  Q3 (Jul) — LTS point release
  Q4 (Oct) — Maintenance release

Each major release gets 2 years of support.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

👥  USERS & PERMISSIONS

This system uses dedicated user accounts with IAM-like permissions.
Instead of 'sudo' for everything, use the right user for the right job:

  admin    → Full system administration (wheel, docker, libvirt)
  dbadmin  → Database operations (postgres, mysql groups)
  webadmin → Web server management (http group)
  ops      → Containers, monitoring, operations (docker, libvirt, journal)
  backup   → Backup & recovery (storage group)

Each group has passwordless sudo access to ONLY its tools.
Members of 'wheel' have full sudo access (password required).

Switch users with:  su - <username>
Or SSH directly:    ssh <user>@<ip>

🛠️  BUILT-IN TOOLS

  acreetionos-profile     — Deployment profiles for 100+ VPS providers
  acreetionos-wizard      — Master setup hub for everything
  acreetionos-systemd     — Complete systemd admin (services, timers,
                           journals, boot analysis, and more)
  acreetionos-toolbox     — Browse & launch 100+ server tools (categorized)
  acreetionos-maintain   — System maintenance menu (updates, firewall,
                           docker, logs, disk health, and more)
  acreetionos-strip-gui  — Remove the desktop, switch to TTY-only
  acreetionos-install-gui — Reinstall the desktop

  Or launch wizards from the Application menu → System → AcreetionOS.

Most tools work without sudo if you're logged in as the right user:

  ops@server    → docker, lazydocker, journalctl
  dbadmin@server → mycli, pgcli, psql, mysql
  webadmin@server → systemctl status nginx, certbot
  admin@server  → everything

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

